node.text: UPDATE: goldfish were returned! I was told these wouldn’t get large and when I brought them back I was told by another person that the first guy was wrong hahahaha. Thanks for the tips yall. Added some beneficial substrate for the plants and replaced them with a small scoop of tetras. A little experiment in propagation. I feed the fish, the fish shit out their butts and the roots are tickled with fecal joy and in return, so am I.

node.text:
Here’s the second illustration for the @rewild “Lost Legends” mission, the Urania sloanus. A supposedly extinct species of moth endemic to Jamaica. The hope is that this species might still exist in some parts of Jamaica and we may be able to reverse its trajectory/ “rediscover” it. Accompanying the illustration are some Jamaican native florals.
#rewild #illustration #science #conservation #nature #jamaica #moth #uraniasloanus

node.text:
GUYS! GOD DAMN!! I have some new killer merch coming your way and as much as I wanted to do a surprise drop, I have to show off the screen print @flashfloodprint did of my floral scorpion design! It’s immaculate. Absolutely perfect. They captured every detail, blade, petal, line, EVERYTHING! Swipe through to see some of the juicy details! These 18X24 posters are huge and are printed with Metallica gold on a dark forest green. Along with these I will drop a shirt with the same gold print and a second design for this summer’s fundraiser/ do good initiative. GAHHHH I’m so fucking happy with these!
#screenprint #scorpion #poster #illustration #nature #science #botany #insects

node.text:
The Thrasher sport was feeling some sort of way and is trying some froggy shit. I’ve never had an entirely albino leaf and whenever these nearly white ones emerge they always fill in with green veining a week or so after unfurling. If this cutting keeps this up we’re looking at a potentially breathtaking plant!
#tylerthrasher #monstera #variegated #houseplants

node.text:
A question from one of my plant consultations yesterday. A client who is just getting into succulents asked “when should I repot these?” Once you’re confident in the soil and potting set up of your succulents, your job is to leave it be for 3-4 years minimum. You should repot only when the container is bulging, root bound or there is something wrong with the soil. Your succulents want to settle in for the long haul so it’s your job to make sure they have an excellent place to call home for a few years AT LEAST.
#planthelp #plantconsultation #tylerthrasher #succulenttips

node.text:
A little family shot of some of my Monstera sports! Mostly comprised of the Thrasher sport. You can see the intense variety of leaves my sport puts out as well as the reward for propagating and taking cuttings. I lost a lot of plants during the move and pandemic depression but everything is slowly growing back and taking root, and I’m growing with them. 
#monsteramonday #variegated #variegation #monstera #houseplants
